 </p>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">The metabolic cost of a passive arousal (i.e. when 
  <span class="italic">T</span>
  <sub>a</sub> or solar radiation would have warmed a roost) was calculated as 1.04 × BMR (
  <a rid="COV070C64" ref-type="bibr" href="#COV070C64">Willis 
   <span class="italic">et al.</span>, 2004
  </a>).
 </p>
 <p xmlns="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">To convert values of mass-specific 
  <div class="inline-formula">
   <div id="ImEquation2" class="math">
    <div class="mrow">
     <div class="msub">
      <div class="mrow">
       <div class="mover">
        <span class="mi">V</span>
        <span class="mo">˙</span>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mrow">
       <div class="mrow">
        <div class="msub">
         <div class="mrow">
          <div class="mrow">
           <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">O</span>
          </div>
         </div>
         <span class="mn">2</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
     </div>
    </div>
   </div>
  </div> into SI units of heat production or energy expenditure (joules per gram per hour), we used Equation 3 from 
  <a rid="COV070C7" ref-type="bibr" href="#COV070C7">Campbell 
   <span class="italic">et al</span>. (2000)
  </a>, which accounts for differences in the catabolism of lipids (L), carbohydrates (C) and proteins (P) in the diet, as follows: 
  <div id="COV070M6" class="disp-formula">
   <span class="label">(6)</span>
   <div id="DmEquation6" class="math">
    <div columnalign="right left" rowspacing=".5em" columnspacing="thickmathspace" class="mtable">
     <div class="mtr">
      <div class="mtd">
       <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">&amp;</span>
       <div class="mrow">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">Heatproduction</span>
        </div>
       </div>
      </div>
      <div class="mtd">
       <span class="mo">=</span>
       <span stretchy="false" class="mo">(</span>
       <span class="mn">17.71</span>
       <div class="mrow">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">P</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">+</span>
       <span class="mn">20.93</span>
       <div class="mrow">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">C</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span class="mo">+</span>
       <span class="mn">19.55</span>
       <div class="mrow">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">L</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <span stretchy="false" class="mo">)</span>
      </div>
     </div>
     <div class="mtr">
      <div class="mtd"/>
      <div class="mtd">
       <span class="mo">×</span>
       <div class="mrow">
        <div class="mrow">
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">mass</span>
         <span class="mo">−</span>
         <span mathvariant="normal" class="mi">specific</span>
        </div>
       </div>
       <div class="mrow">
        <span width="0.056em" class="mspace"/>
       </div>
       <div class="mrow">
        <div class="msub">
         <div class="mrow">
